<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-710-759  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 710 759.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  Dec 1990 v27 n12 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New York airports speed auto traffic. (fiber-optic networks)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Port Authority of New York and New Jersey will spend $33.5million for a fiber-optic network revenue-control system atKennedy, La Guardia and Newark International airports.andP;  The systemwill track traffic in parking lots, allowing customers to payparking with credit cards or cash at automated parking machines.andO;Long exit lines at parking lots will be eliminated, along with thechance for human error.andP;  The configuration proposed will be afiber-based, drop-and-insert, counter rotating ring.andP;  Using atime-division multiplexing technique, data is transmitted back tothe host computer.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     AutomobilesData CommunicationsNetwork ManagementAirportsFiber optics.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographchart.andO;Caption:   Counter rotating fiber optic ring. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>